headline: Is Now the Right Time to Reassess IBM’s Value After AI Partnership Announcements?
summary: Wondering if International Business Machines (IBM) stock is still a smart buy? You are not alone. The company has a reputation as a tech giant and a history of innovation. IBM’s stock has surged an impressive 35.2% year-to-date and a remarkable 208.0% over the last five years. However, it has seen a slight pullback of 2.7% in the past week. Investor enthusiasm has grown recently following announcements about IBM’s expanding AI partnerships and its strategic moves in cloud computing and...

headline: IBM Is an AI and IT Leader Set for Growth, Says Analyst. Plus, Lowe’s, Rocket, and More Stocks.
summary: Lowe’s shares are seeing a relief rally, as third-quarter results cleared a very low bar, following weak results out of  Home Depot  Lowe’s comps slightly outperformed its larger peer, with that occurring only once in the prior eight quarters.  There’s upside near $1/share if gross margins get back above 3.25%, which is still far from the pandemic highs of 4.5% when the stock went public.
